  stimulus_text = 'The author of the novel, who is known for his realistic depictions of life in the American south, was a bit of a rebel in his writing, choosing to avoid the conventions of traditional Southern literature. He rejected the sentimentalism of the genre, choosing to portray the harsh realities of poverty and racism. Instead of focusing on idyllic settings and romanticized characters, he chose to depict the dark side of the region. He rejected the melodramatic language that was often found in Southern novels, choosing instead to write in a more straightforward and direct style. What is the most likely reason why the author decided to reject the conventions of traditional Southern literature?',
